   {:e #blake3 "b72fed9684051c9ea4dcd26e95360d37c48cb6a521d0e57dc861653be0e656d2" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-08c9dcb2\nCONCEPT-MULTI + FRONTIER-STEER IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS — EXACT API CHANGES: IN CONCEPT.RS: (1) New function: pub fn assign_to_concepts(store: &Store, embedding: &[f32], threshold: f32) -> Vec<ConceptAssignment>. Implementation: iterate find_nearest_concept logic but collect ALL matches above threshold, not just best. Sort by similarity descending. Return vec. (2) New function: pub fn co_occurrence_matrix(store: &Store) -> Vec<(EntityId, EntityId, f64)>. For each concept pair, compute Jaccard of member observation sets. Member sets from :exploration/concept Refs. Return triples (concept_a, concept_b, jaccard). (3) New struct FrontierRec { pub kind: FrontierKind, pub target: String, pub score: f64, pub rationale: String }. pub enum FrontierKind { Explore, Deepen, Bridge }. (4) New function: pub fn frontier_recommendation(store: &Store, current_embedding: &[f32]) -> Option<FrontierRec>. Computes explore/deepen/bridge candidates and returns the highest-scoring one. IN OBSERVE.RS: (5) Replace: let concept_assignment = assign_to_concept(store, &obs_embedding, threshold). With: let assignments = assign_to_concepts(store, &obs_embedding, threshold). Write :exploration/concept Ref for EACH assignment. Update centroid for EACH matched concept. (6) Replace: compute_steering_question(store, &assignment, &matches). With: frontier_recommendation(store, &obs_embedding). Format: '→ explore: target — rationale' or '→ deepen: ...' or '→ bridge: ...'. (7) Primary concept (first in sorted assignments) shown as 'concept:X (N obs, surprise=S)'. Secondary concepts shown as '+ Y (cosine=C)'. IN STATUS.RS: (8) Add coupled pairs, bridge gaps, and frontier to concept section of status output. IN SCHEMA.RS: (9) No schema changes needed — :exploration/concept is already Cardinality::Many.; FRONTIER-STEER IMPLEMENTATION SPEC: The observe response becomes three lines: (1) STORED: 'observed: :observation/slug (+N datoms)' — what was captured. (2) CONCEPTS: 'concept:X (N obs, surprise=S) + Y (cosine=C)' — primary + secondary memberships. The primary is the best match (highest cosine). Secondaries are others above threshold, shown with cosine score. (3) FRONTIER: '→ explore/deepen/bridge: target — rationale'. Computed by frontier_recommendation(store, obs_embedding). The three frontier types: EXPLORE = unexplored entity with highest connectivity. Implementation: count :exploration/mentions-entity Refs pointing to each :pkg/* entity. Packages with 0 mentions but imported by packages WITH mentions score highest. Score = count(explored_importers). Data source: bootstrap detection at init already creates :pkg/* entities. Dependency edges come from Go import analysis (or can be inferred from co-mention patterns). DEEPEN = concept with highest variance and >= 3 members. Implementation: concept_inventory_with_innate already returns variance. Filter to variance > 0.5 and member_count >= 3. Score = variance * member_count. Rationale includes the concept name and suggests investigating that concept IN the context of what was just observed. BRIDGE = pair of concepts with high member counts but zero co-occurring observations (multi-membership gap). Implementation: co_occurrence_matrix gives Jaccard for each pair. Pairs with Jaccard = 0 but both member_count >= 3 are bridge candidates. Score = member_count_a * member_count_b (potential connections). The highest-scoring recommendation across all three types wins. Tie-break: explore > deepen > bridge (exploration bias for early sessions, deepening bias for mature sessions — could be session-stage-aware later). STATUS ADDITIONS: format_concept_status gains three new sections: (1) 'coupled: X ↔ Y (N shared observations)' for pairs with Jaccard > 0.3. (2) 'bridge gap: X ↔ Y (0 shared, N connecting packages)' for pairs with Jaccard = 0 but structural connection. (3) 'frontier: pkg1, pkg2, pkg3 (high connectivity, 0 observations)' — top 3 unexplored entities by connectivity score. CLI FLOW: observe.rs after concept assignment calls frontier_recommendation(store, &obs_embedding). The result replaces compute_steering_question. The old steering question becomes the fallback when frontier returns None (empty store, no bootstrap packages)." :op :assert}
